# Safety Rails

## Required Reading Before Changes

| Trigger | Required reading |
|---------|-----------------|
| Modifying `pkg/api/v*` types | `docs/agent-guides/api-type-system.md` |
| Adding/changing VM sizes | `docs/agent-guides/azure-product-constraints.md` |
| Touching `pkg/cluster`, `pkg/util/cluster`, or `pkg/deploy` | `docs/agent-guides/package-deployment-context.md` |
| Changing Makefile, CI, or build targets | `docs/agent-guides/multi-module-build.md` |

## Architecture Invariant

Cluster mutations (PUT/DELETE) are **async**: Frontend writes to CosmosDB with non-terminal state, Backend polls and processes, then updates with terminal state. **Never bypass this** — frontend handlers must NOT perform cluster operations directly.

## Where Code Runs

| Runtime context | Packages |
|----------------|----------|
| RP control plane (Azure VMSS) | `pkg/frontend`, `pkg/backend`, `pkg/cluster`, `pkg/monitor`, `pkg/gateway`, `pkg/portal` |
| Customer OpenShift cluster | `pkg/operator/controllers` (26 controllers) |
| CI/dev only (NOT production) | `pkg/util/cluster`, `hack/cluster`, `test/e2e` |
| RP infra deployment | `pkg/deploy` |

**Never mix runtime contexts** — e.g. don't import `pkg/util/cluster` (CI-only) from `pkg/frontend` (production RP).

## Manual Approval Required

The following actions are **never** to be run autonomously. Always ask the user for explicit confirmation first:

- **`git push`** / **`git push --force`** — publishes commits to the remote
- **`gh pr create`** — opens a public pull request
- **`gh pr merge`** — merges code into the target branch
- **`git rebase`** — rewrites commit history, can cause conflicts
- **`make client`** / **`client-generate`** — destructive: deletes all generated SDK clients before regenerating. If Docker/autorest fails mid-run, restore with `git checkout -- pkg/client/ python/client/`
- **`make generate`** — modifies many files via code generation; commit current work first
- **Deleting branches** (`git branch -D`, `git push origin --delete`)
- **Deleting or overwriting local config** (`.env`, `secrets/`, `dev-config.yaml`, kubeconfig files)
- **`git reset --hard`**, **`git checkout -- <path>`** on uncommitted work
- **`--no-verify`** on any git command — never skip pre-commit hooks
